&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TITLE OF POST:&lt;/strong&gt;                              &lt;strong&gt;PRACTICE NURSE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GRADE:&lt;/strong&gt;                                             AFC Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HOURS OF EMPLOYMENT:&lt;/strong&gt;          Up to Full time / Negotiable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;APPOINTMENT:&lt;/strong&gt;                              Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBLE TO:&lt;/strong&gt;                          Nurse Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ACCOUNTABLE TO:                      &lt;/strong&gt;The Partners&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BASE:                                         &lt;/strong&gt;Working flexibly between our sites &lt;strong&gt;- &lt;/strong&gt;Tibshelf, Stonebroom and Holmewood &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are offering an opportunity to join a well-established team of nurses and GPs as a Practice Nurse. We are a friendly, innovative practice, rated as Outstanding practice by the Care Quality Commission and have a focus on delivery of the highest quality of care for our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an innovative team player to join our busy nursing team, who can contribute to and influence the development of nursing services provided within primary care.  The post is for a Fully Qualified Practice Nurse,  previous experience is a must  You will be fully supported by a team of Nurse Clinicians, Practice Nurses; Treatment Room Nurses, Health Care Assistants and management and administration staff. The role will encompass chronic disease management, health promotion, family planning, cytology and immunisation, ear care and wound care in line with local and national guidelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Situated in a semi-rural community, close to the Peak district we have 16,955 patients, provide services over 4 sites and utilise the clinical system SystmOne.  We are a training practice for Doctors, GP’s, Medical Students and Student Nurses. We offer above average salary and terms and conditions in line with NHS Agenda for Change. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries and visits are welcomed, please contact Ruth Cater, Practice Manager on 01773 309040, or Sue Cartledge, Nurse Manager on 01773 309030.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date Sunday 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
